main event: Two bright orange-like, slow-moving, non-rigid, and oblong-shaped objects were observed on ground radar for 30 minutes.
interesting points: The objects disappeared from both the radar scope and visual sighting.
A second similar object was also observed by the same observer.
The report suggests the objects could be a satellite, asteroid, or aircraft, but the observations don't clearly indicate any of these.
There were several other sightings of objects in the same general area and timeframe.
The report indicates the objects were making a brisk maneuver to the east after 4-5 minutes of observation.
